descriptions: We now have a new simple landing website for our project (hosted on EPFL infrastructure)
Moved the git repository from Grenoble-hosted to a more neutrally branded https://gitlab.com/spam-project/spam

Organisation of a workshop to present spam to researchers and help them get started on analysis problems
Scientific workshop on spam software and digital image/volume correlation organized with hands-on sessions, theoretical foundations, and expert-led tutorials.
The presentations from the workshop are openly available in the form of ipython notebooks to be used with RISE
Spam is now installed as a loadable module on PSI’s Ra cluster
Around 30 workshop attendees, and many more due to improved website, documentation and installability
